benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/renameKey - Update a bundle externalKey

covered: Successful update of bundle external key (TC01)
Update with missing required header X-Killbill-CreatedBy (TC02)
Update with externalKey already used by another bundle (TC05)
Update with missing externalKey in body (TC08)
Update with extra fields in body (TC09)
Update with X-Killbill-Reason and X-Killbill-Comment headers (TC14)
Update when no bundles exist in the system (TC15)
Concurrent updates to the same bundle (TC17)
Regression - update with previously problematic externalKey (TC18)
Update with special characters in externalKey (TC19)
Update with trailing/leading spaces in externalKey (TC20)
gaps: No tests explicitly cover authorization and permission checks beyond missing headers.
No scenarios test rate limiting or throttling behavior.
Caching headers and cache validation are not tested.
No explicit tests for concurrency conflicts or race conditions beyond basic concurrency scenario.
Performance testing for response time under load is only partially addressed in TC23.
No tests for system recovery or fallback mechanisms in case of service unavailability.
recommendations: Add explicit authorization and permission validation tests, including role-based access control.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to verify system stability under high request volume.
Include tests for caching headers such as ETag and Cache-Control to ensure proper cache validation.
Develop more detailed concurrency and race condition tests, including simultaneous updates and conflict resolution.
Enhance performance testing with more comprehensive load and stress scenarios, including response time metrics under various loads.
Add recovery and fallback scenario tests for system component failures, such as database or service outages.
